adjective.description: Relating to the English royal dynasty which held the throne from the accession of Henry II in 1154 until the death of Richard III in 1485.

noun.description: A member of the Plantagenet dynasty.

origin: From Latin planta genista sprig of broom, said to be worn as a crest by and given as a nickname to Geoffrey, count of Anjou, the father of Henry II.
